        "text_RqTiqW": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>When Tim Hanson acquired Pro Ball, he saw an opportunity to do things differently. Custom golf balls were being produced in factories with standard turnaround times that often exceeded a month, leaving the promotional industry underserved in both speed and service. Tim flipped the business model, starting with the name. He changed it from Pro Ball to Ball Pro, reflecting a commitment to a new approach built on faster turnaround, better service, and a commitment to doing things right.</p><p><strong>Built on Family Values</strong><br/>Tim led Ball Pro the same way he lived his life, grounded in family, respect, and doing right by people. He believed that how you treat your team matters just as much as the work you deliver, and he showed up for his employees with care, consistency, and integrity. That mindset shaped the foundation of Ball Pro, and it still guides us today. Even as we’ve grown, we’ve stayed true to what mattered most, putting people first and building a culture rooted in respect. It’s a commitment we’re proud to see recognized as one of Counselor’s Best Places to Work, and one we’ll continue to carry forward.<br/><br/></p>",
            "subtext_color": true
          }
        }
